The distant mountains rise before me,
Carved from ancient stone,
I wander to where the winds sing
And find my heart's true home.

Valleys cradle every heartbeat,
Heights kiss the morning sun,
And nature dances in existence—
Our wild journey has begun.

— Mountain Song

- Lola Ridge
